 ## [Unreleased]
 
+## [0.6.0] - 2026-05-30
+
+Sixth alpha. The "Contribution Gate" milestone: the project flips
+from solo development mode to OPEN for outside contributions on top
+of a hardened release pipeline. Ships sigstore-signed wheel + sdist
++ SBOM (CycloneDX 1.6 JSON), SLSA Build L2 provenance, audit.yml
+PR-time supply-chain scan (pip-audit dual-mode + dependency-review),
+Dependabot v2 with ungrouped security updates, zizmor workflow
+static-analysis, contributor docs (CONTRIBUTING flow, TRIAGE guide,
+LABEL-TAXONOMY, path-scoped CODEOWNERS, 3 issue templates), SECURITY
+severity-tier SLOs, MAINTAINER-RUNBOOK, and a release-gate extended
+from 8 to 14 checks.
+
+### Added
+
+- **Sigstore-signed release artifacts.** `release.yml` signs the
+  wheel, sdist, and both CycloneDX 1.6 JSON SBOMs (clean + dev-otel)
+  via `sigstore/gh-action-sigstore-python`. Bundles upload to the
+  GitHub Release page automatically. SLSA Build L2 provenance via
+  two `actions/attest-build-provenance` invocations; SBOM
+  attestations via two `actions/attest-sbom` invocations.
+- **User-facing trust-chain verifier.** `scripts/verify_release.py`
+  runs FIVE checks: wheel-signature, sdist-signature, tag-signature,
+  sbom-signature, changelog-cross-ref. Pure stdlib; shells out to
+  `python -m sigstore verify identity` with the workflow-scoped
+  exact-match identity `https://github.com/Ridou/horus-os/.github/workflows/release.yml@refs/tags/v<version>`.
+- **PR-time supply-chain scan.** `audit.yml` runs pip-audit
+  (osv + pypi sources) on `[dev]` and `[dev,otel]` install variants,
+  plus `actions/dependency-review-action` for license allowlist
+  enforcement. Honors `.github/pip-audit-ignore.txt` with dated-
+  reason discipline; per-CVE tracking docs under
+  `.github/pip-audit-tracking/`.
+- **Dependabot v2.** `pip` and `github-actions` ecosystems, weekly
+  cadence, cooldown windows (3 days default, 14 days semver-major),
+  four version-updates groups (ai-sdks, otel, web-stack, dev-tools).
+  Security updates are explicitly UNGROUPED: every CVE gets its own
+  PR labelled `security-update`.
+- **zizmor workflow static analysis.** `.github/workflows/zizmor.yml`
+  runs on every PR that touches `.github/workflows/**`; SARIF lands
+  in the Security tab.
+- **Contributor docs + templates.** CONTRIBUTING.md updated with the
+  active contribution flow (claim-then-PR, 7-day acknowledgement,
+  related decisions section). New `docs/TRIAGE.md` documents the
+  Sunday-triage cadence + good-first-issue rubric + claim flow.
+  New `docs/LABEL-TAXONOMY.md` documents the 15-label hard cap with
+  saved-reply text per label. Path-scoped `.github/CODEOWNERS`
+  (workflows, release scripts, SECURITY, planning). Three issue
+  templates: bug, feature, security (private-reporting redirect).
+  Four decision files: no-cla, no-stale-bot, sigstore-keyless,
+  sbom-cyclonedx, no-pypi-in-v0.6.
+- **SECURITY refresh.** Severity-tier SLOs (Critical 14d, High 30d,
+  Medium 90d, Low none). Over-capacity escalation path.
+  Test-advisory ritual.
+- **Maintainer runbook.** `docs/MAINTAINER-RUNBOOK.md` extends
+  `docs/RELEASE.md` with the gitsign signed-tag procedure, the
+  release.yml outputs to verify, `gh attestation verify` commands,
+  one-time repo settings checklist, and the `accepted-for-review`
+  30-day throttle for post-flip PR queue management.
+- **Release-gate extended to 14 checks.** Five Phase 57 checks
+  (release-workflow-signing-present, release-workflow-sbom-present,
+  audit-workflow-present, local-pip-audit-clean,
+  actions-pinned-by-sha) plus Phase 53-followup sbom-matches-wheel.
+  Two-tier execution model: `--tier local` (under 10s, grep-only)
+  vs `--tier release` (full network + scan). `--allow-offline`
+  short-circuits network checks with SKIP semantics.
+- **Pitfall regression suite.** `tests/test_contribution_gate_pitfalls/`
+  ships 12+ regression tests, one per pitfall in
+  `.planning/research/PITFALLS.md` (mirrors v0.5 TEST-17 pattern).
+
+### Changed
+
+- **Contribution gate flipped OPEN.** STATUS.md, README.md,
+  CONTRIBUTING.md, SECURITY.md, the PR template, and the issue
+  templates all updated to reflect the post-flip state. The
+  `issue-claim-watcher.yml` workflow is removed (no longer needed
+  now that claims are honored per the documented flow).
+- **SECURITY.md supported versions.** v0.5.x and v0.6.x supported;
+  earlier lines retired.
+
+### Removed
+
+- `.github/workflows/issue-claim-watcher.yml` (the canned-reply
+  automation; obsolete after the gate flip).
+
